The paper deals with steganalysis of color images using deep neural networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional layers and their impact on the detection performance, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the security aspect of steganography, which falls under the cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category.
